# TDD workflow

## Default order

1. Write or update a failing test in `tests/` that describes the behavior
2. Implement the smallest change to make it pass
3. Refactor without changing behavior
4. Run `npm test` before every commit

## What gets tests first

- Domain logic: `src/domain/*` (risk engine, briefing validation, evidence checks)
- Pure functions and Zod schemas before UI wiring
- API route behavior via service-layer tests when possible

## What can skip upfront tests

- One-off layout/CSS tweaks
- README and copy changes (unless they embed dynamic examples)

## Pre-commit gate

Husky runs `npm test` on every commit. Do not commit broken tests. Fix or revert before staging.
